utf8Encode

public static final java.lang.String utf8Encode(java.lang.String toEncode)
UTF-8 encodes a string using URLEncode.encode(toEncode, "UTF-8") with the added caveat that it also encodes spaces as %20. This is typically used to encode strings that need to be decoded in JavaScript using decodeURIComponent; because URLEncode.encode replaces spaces with + signs, and decodeURIComponent does not decode + signs as spaces, but leaves them as a + signs. This method also catches UnsupportedEncodingException and throws a RuntimeException if it were to occur.

Parameters:
toEncode - The string to encode
Returns:
The UTF-8 encoded string (with spaces converted to %20)
